<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="195" pageId="4" pageNumber="194" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[159,1156,1522,1722]" box="[160,276,1522,1548]" pageId="4" pageNumber="194">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,1522,1548]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="194">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[159,1156,1522,1722]" lastBlockId="5.[159,1155,1199,1328]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="195" pageId="4" pageNumber="194">
<taxonomicName box="[160,282,1558,1583]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Gibboryctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[160,282,1558,1583]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="194">Gibboryctes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is separated from other Neotropical Oryctini by the following combination of characters: inconspicuous sexual dimorphism (
<figureCitation box="[667,762,1593,1618]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[160,227,1366,1389]" captionTargetBox="[162,1148,150,1331]" captionTargetId="figure-77@4.[162,1154,142,1335]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi, 1974. (a,b) Holotype male in dorsal and lateral views, respectively; (c) labels; (d,e) male habitus in dorsal and lateral views, respectively; (f) female habitus in dorsal view. (a,b) pictures out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758317" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758317/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="194">Figures 1</figureCitation>
(d–f) and 3(a–c)); transverse head, 2 times wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[406,493,1627,1652]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1146,1169]" captionTargetBox="[184,1146,142,1069]" captionTargetId="figure-59@12.[166,1149,142,1114]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 9. Detail of head, pronotum and prothoracic legs of males in dorsal view: (a) Gibboryctes szelenyii (Endrödi); (b) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov.; (c) Heterogomphus gracilicornis Prell; (d) Tetragus waldenfelsi (Endrödi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758337/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="194">Figure 9</figureCitation>
(a,b));both sexes with a transverse tubercle on head (
<figureCitation box="[1058,1155,1627,1652]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1146,1169]" captionTargetBox="[184,1146,142,1069]" captionTargetId="figure-59@12.[166,1149,142,1114]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 9. Detail of head, pronotum and prothoracic legs of males in dorsal view: (a) Gibboryctes szelenyii (Endrödi); (b) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov.; (c) Heterogomphus gracilicornis Prell; (d) Tetragus waldenfelsi (Endrödi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758337/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="194">Figures 9</figureCitation>
(a,b) and 11(a–c)); bidentate mandibles with subapical tooth backward produced and larger than apical tooth (
<figureCitation box="[408,514,1697,1722]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="10.[160,225,1156,1179]" captionTargetBox="[169,1149,148,1090]" captionTargetId="figure-156@10.[166,1149,142,1125]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 7. Right mandible in dorsal view. (a) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi; (b) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (c) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov.; (d) Heterogomphus gracilicornis Prell; (e) Tetragus waldenfelsi (Endrödi). Red arrows indicate the apical tooth in (a–e), striate molar in (d)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758333/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="194">Figure 7</figureCitation>
(a–c)); inner margin of galea bearing small teeth; pronotum with no horns,with only a small tubercle on anterior area combined with a shallow or absent concavity (
<figureCitation box="[391,492,1234,1259]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1146,1169]" captionTargetBox="[184,1146,142,1069]" captionTargetId="figure-59@12.[166,1149,142,1114]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 9. Detail of head, pronotum and prothoracic legs of males in dorsal view: (a) Gibboryctes szelenyii (Endrödi); (b) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov.; (c) Heterogomphus gracilicornis Prell; (d) Tetragus waldenfelsi (Endrödi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758337/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="195">Figures 9</figureCitation>
(a,b) and 
<figureCitation box="[597,708,1234,1259]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="14.[160,225,1441,1464]" captionTargetBox="[168,1146,144,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-42@14.[166,1149,142,1410]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 11. Detail of head, pronotum and prothoracic legs of females in dorsal view: (a) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi;(b) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (c) Gibboryctes endroedi sp.nov.; (d) Heterogomphus gracilicornis Prell; (e) Tetragus waldenfelsi (Endrödi). Arrow indicates punctate frons in (b)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="195">Figures 11</figureCitation>
(a–c)); elytra with dense, large and deep punctures (
<figureCitation box="[285,391,1268,1293]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="15.[160,225,1189,1212]" captionTargetBox="[167,1149,146,1154]" captionTargetId="figure-100@15.[166,1149,142,1157]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 12. Females of Gibboryctes species with detail of head, pronotum and prothoracic legs in lateral view and left elytra in dorsal view, respectively. (a,b) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi; (c,d) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (e,f) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov. Jsi, juxtasutural interstria. Arrow indicates coalescent punctures in (e)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758343/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="195">Figure 12</figureCitation>
(b,d,f)); ventrite VI 2 times longer than ventrite V in female (
<figureCitation box="[1051,1155,1268,1293]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="16.[160,225,1058,1081]" captionTargetBox="[166,1146,145,1023]" captionTargetId="figure-155@16.[166,1149,142,1026]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 13. Detail of ventrites I–VI of females. (a) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi; (b) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov; (c) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov.; (d) Tetragus waldenfelsi (Endrödi). Red arrows indicate the proportions of ventrites V and VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758345/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="195">Figure 13</figureCitation>
(a–c)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
