<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,388,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="202">Sexual dimorphism</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[160,1155,1269,1399]" pageId="12" pageNumber="202">
The two sexes are largely identical, but the female can be distinguished in the following aspects: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[254,316,1340,1365]" pageId="12" pageNumber="202">Head</emphasis>
: Anterior clypeal margin rounded. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[701,818,1340,1365]" pageId="12" pageNumber="202">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Tergite VIII flattened in lateral view; ventrite VI parabolic, lacking posterior emargination.
</paragraph>
